deep_analysis.executive_summary: ALL 15 executions follow an IDENTICAL failure pattern. Every single execution returns 'Information not available in the knowledge graph.' because a cascading authentication failure breaks the entire pipeline. The root cause is a 401 'User not found' error from the OpenRouter API, which prevents BOTH entity extraction AND embedding generation, causing ALL downstream nodes to operate on empty/error data.

root_cause_chain.impact: CRITICAL - No entities extracted, so Neo4j Query Builder gets no entities and sets skip_neo4j=true. This means the graph database is NEVER queried.
root_cause_chain.cascading_effect: Neo4j Query Builder -> skip_neo4j=true -> Shield #4 sends empty statement -> Neo4j returns 400 error

root_cause_chain.impact: CRITICAL - No embedding generated, so Validate Embedding fails (got 0 dims, expected 1536). Pinecone search fails because no vector is provided.
root_cause_chain.cascading_effect: Validate Embedding -> error -> Pinecone HyDE Search -> 400 "vector or ID must be provided"

root_cause_chain.impact: HIGH - With both Neo4j and Pinecone returning errors/empty results, the merge node crashes on undefined data.
root_cause_chain.cascading_effect: Empty merge results -> Reranker has nothing to rerank -> 429 rate limit error (still calls API with empty data)

root_cause_chain.impact: MEDIUM - Reranker is being called even when there is nothing to rerank, wasting API calls and hitting rate limits.
root_cause_chain.cascading_effect: Reranker Fallback Handler activates -> empty results -> Token Budgeting gets 0 tokens

root_cause_chain.impact: CRITICAL - Even if context were available, the LLM call itself fails with the same auth error. Answer Formatter gracefully handles this by returning "Information not available."
root_cause_chain.cascading_effect: Answer Formatter produces fallback response -> "Information not available in the knowledge graph."

openrouter_401_user_not_found.description: OpenRouter API returns 401 "User not found" for all LLM/embedding calls. This is likely an expired API key, wrong model endpoint, or account issue.
openrouter_401_user_not_found.fix: Verify and update the OpenRouter API key in the n8n workflow credentials. Check if the arcee-ai/trinity-large-preview:free model is still available.

neo4j_empty_statement.description: Neo4j receives an empty/null Cypher statement because entity extraction failed upstream.
neo4j_empty_statement.fix: This will self-resolve once the OpenRouter auth issue is fixed (entities will be extracted).

pinecone_no_vector.description: Pinecone query sent without a vector because embedding generation failed upstream.
pinecone_no_vector.fix: This will self-resolve once the OpenRouter auth issue is fixed (embeddings will be generated).

cohere_rate_limit.description: Cohere reranker hits 429 rate limit. May be calling with empty documents which still costs a request.
cohere_rate_limit.fix: Add a guard before the reranker to skip if there are no documents to rerank. Also investigate Cohere rate limits for the current plan.

merge_undefined_read.description: JavaScript error at line 141 reading property 0 of undefined. The merge node does not handle the case where both sources return errors.
merge_undefined_read.fix: Add null checks in the merge node JS code at line 141. Should gracefully handle when Neo4j and/or Pinecone return error objects instead of result arrays.

pipeline_flow_analysis.note: Despite 7 nodes with errors, the execution still "succeeds" because fallback handlers gracefully degrade to an "Information not available" response. The workflow never throws an unhandled exception - it just produces useless answers.

recommended_fixes.details: The OpenRouter API key (sk-or-v1-d229e5f...) is returning 401 "User not found". Either the key is expired/revoked, the account is suspended, or the model endpoint has changed. This single fix will unblock 3 nodes: HyDE & Entity Extraction, Generate HyDE Embedding, and LLM Answer Synthesis.
recommended_fixes.expected_impact: Restores the entire pipeline to functional state

recommended_fixes.action: Add null safety to Merge Graph + Vector + Community (Deep) node at line 141
recommended_fixes.details: Even after the auth fix, edge cases where Neo4j or Pinecone return errors should be handled gracefully. Add null/undefined checks before accessing array indices.
recommended_fixes.expected_impact: Prevents JS crashes when upstream data sources fail partially

recommended_fixes.action: Add guard before Cohere Reranker to skip when input is empty
recommended_fixes.details: The reranker is called even with 0 documents, wasting API quota and hitting rate limits. Add a conditional check: if merged_results is empty, bypass reranker entirely.
recommended_fixes.expected_impact: Saves API quota and eliminates unnecessary 429 errors
